<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2464</anchor> <rss>dannypsnl.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Person</taxon> <addr>dannypsnl</addr>  <route>dannypsnl.xml</route>   <title>Lîm Tsú-thuàn</title> <meta name="external">https://dannypsnl.me/</meta><meta name="position">Compiler Developer</meta><meta name="institution">Second State</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter/> <backmatter><contributions/> <context/> <related/> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2465</anchor> <rss>jms-009Q.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Changelog</taxon> <addr>jms-009Q</addr>  <route>jms-009Q.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>9</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Forester 2.5 [unreleased]</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Thanks to <link href="dannypsnl.xml" type="local" title="Lîm Tsú-thuàn">Lîm Tsú-thuàn</link> and <link href="vikramanchoudhury.xml" type="local" title="Vikraman Choudhury">Vikraman Choudhury</link> for their suggestions and bug reports on the <link href="https://lists.sr.ht/~jonsterling/forester-discuss" type="external">mailing list</link>.</p><ul>  <li>A new <code>\iftex</code> command has been added, following a suggestion of <link href="vikramanchoudhury.xml" type="local" title="Vikraman Choudhury">Vikraman Choudhury</link>; this can be used to control the behavior of macros, depending on whether they are being rendered by <tex>\LaTeX</tex> or by the browser. For example, <code>\iftex{foo}{bar}</code> will become <code>foo</code> when passed to the <tex>\LaTeX</tex> tool, but will be reated as <code>bar</code> when rendering for the browser.</li></ul></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2466</anchor> <rss>2023-09-23.rss.xml</rss> <taxo